ell functioning markets to assess the links between land and labor markets market imperfections institutional rigidities or other entry barriers either prevent market s from operating or lead to undesirable outcomes we use a large nationally data set that is representative for china's rural areas we find that households with limited endowments of land and higher agricultural ability and from villages with less restriction on land transfer in terms of to whom to rent and types of land to rent tend to rent in land and a well functioning of land transfer markets facilitates the emergence of labor markets download pdf+ complete modified april 2007 pdf migration_and_migration_workin pdf 99.9 kb topics economic development china search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest efficiency of land allocation through tenancy markets evidence from china scott rozelle shingo kimura keijiro otsuka pdf+ development of groundwater markets in china a glimpse into progress to date lijuan zhang jinxia wang jikun huang scott rozelle world development vol 36 4 2008 html+ cover the autumn harvest peasants and markets in post collective rural china xueguang zhou the china quarterly vol 208 2011 html+ cover rural development in china new challenges in a new landscape scott rozelle world bank policy note 2003 pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
